esheet&quot; href=&quot;https://s3.amazonaws.com/assets.sbnation.com/ csk/uploads/verge-toc.css&quot;>; &lt;div class=&quot;duet--article--article-body-component verge-table-of-contents border-franklin border&quot; id=&quot;toc-main&quot;>;&lt;/div >; &lt;/div>; &lt;h2 id=&quot;w5Bj9P&quot;>;最好的智能...&lt;/h2>; &lt;p>; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theverge.com/23901327/amazon-october-prime-day -best-early-deals-tech-echo-speakers-fire-tvs-2023&quot;>;继续阅读&amp;hellip;&lt;/a>; &lt;/p>; </content><link href="https://www.theverge.com/23901327/amazon-october-prime-day-best-early-deals-tech-echo-speakers-fire-tvs-2023" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/><id> https://www.theverge.com/23901327/amazon-october-prime-day-best-early-deals-tech-echo-speakers-fire-tvs-2023</id><author><name>希娜·瓦萨尼</name></author></entry><entry><published>2023-10-06T13:54:53-04:00</published><updated> 2023-10-06T13:54:53-04:00</updated><title>联想高管承诺，到 2025 年，其 80% 的设备将可供消费者维修</title><content type="html">&lt;figure>; &lt;img alt=&quot;联想的可卷曲笔记本电脑概念坐在桌子上，屏幕完全展开。&quot; src=&quot;https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/NBqyN1bec-wdqrMU5o0EEirMED0=/0x0:6240x4160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72728909/DSCF0016.0.jpeg&quot; />; &lt;figcaption>;&lt;a class=&quot;ql-link&quot; href=&quot;https://www.theverge.com/2023/2/26/23615842/lenovo-rollable-laptop-smartphone-prototype-concept&quot; target=&quot; _blank&quot;>;&lt;em>;联想的可卷曲笔记本电脑概念。&lt;/em>;&lt;/a>; | &lt;em>;摄影：Jon Porter / The Verge&lt;/em>;&lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p id=&quot;I689xH&quot;>;起初，联想似乎只是随意地嫉妒 Framework 的 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www .theverge.com/23725039/framework-laptop-13-2023-intel-review&quot;>;模块化可修复笔记本电脑&lt;/a>; - 首先，它发送了&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theverge.com/2022/8 /19/23312697/lenovo-framework-laptop-power-button-trademark-infringement&quot;>;对 Framework 电源按钮的停止&lt;/a>;，然后推出了自己的模块化概念笔记本电脑，称为 &lt;a href=&quot; https://www.theverge.com/2023/7/17/23797765/lenovo-ponders-repairable-laptops-with-project-aurora&quot;>;Project Aurora&lt;/a>; 不承诺实际构建这样的东西。&lt; /p>; &lt;p id=&quot;eB0idl&quot;>;但看来 ThinkPad 和摩托罗拉的所有者实际上可能很认真地提高可修复性。联想高管卢卡·罗西 (Luca Rossi) 在 2023 年 Canalys 欧洲、中东和非洲论坛上表示：“我们 80% 以上的设备都可以在客户处维修”，&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theregister.com/2023/10/05 /lenovo_pc_boss_4_in/&quot;>;根据&lt;em>;The Register&lt;/em>;&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p id=&quot;4jyGGY&quot;>;“电池、SSD，很多东西将不再密封在产品中，但客户可以在现场进行维修，从而节省大量浪费。”据报道，他说道。 &lt;/p>; &lt;div class=&quot;c-float-left c-float-hang&quot;>;&lt;aside id=&quot;CMhyWm&quot;>;&lt;div data-anthem-component=&quot;readmore&quot; data-anthem-component-data=&#39;{ &quot;stories&quot;:[{&quot;title&quot;:&quot;自己修手机的时代已经来临&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.theverge.com/23017361/ifixit-right-to-repair-parts- google-samsung-valve-microsoft&quot;},{&quot;title&quot;:&quot;修复权：所有最新新闻和更新&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.theverge.com/2023/5/28/23738770 /right-to-repair-updates-laws&quot;},{&quot;title&quot;:&quot;了解欧盟争取用户可更换智能手机电池的斗争&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.theverge.com/2023/ 6/24/23771064/european-union-battery-regulation-ecodesign-user-replacable-batteries&quot;}]}&#39;>;&lt;/div>;&lt;/aside>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p id=&quot;61xzIG&quot;>;L.. .&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theverge.com/2023/10/6/23884108/lenovo-consumer-repair-pcs-serviceability-framework&quot;>;继续阅读&amp;hellip;&lt;/a >; &lt;/p>; </content><link href="https://www.theverge.com/2023/10/6/23884108/lenovo-consumer-repair-pcs-serviceability-framework" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/><id> https://www.theverge.com/2023/10/6/23884108/lenovo-consumer-repair-pcs-serviceability-framework</id><author><name>肖恩·霍利斯特</name></author></entry></feed>